    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-01-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-01-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="64"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d64">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1" type="from"
                            >Roosevelt</persName> to Marshal <persName corresp="#p_S16" type="to"
                            >Stalin</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d64fn1">Sent to the United States Naval Attaché, Moscow, via
                        Navy channels.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-01-22">22 January
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Number 178, Top Secret and Personal, from the President to Marshal <persName
                        corresp="#p_S16">Stalin</persName>.</p>
                <p>I have decided to not have any press representatives at <gloss
                        target="#t_ARGONAUT1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Argonaut</hi>
                    </gloss> and to permit only a small group of uniformed service photographers
                    from the American Navy to take the pictures that we will want.</p>
                <p>Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CWS1">Churchill</persName> agrees.<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d64fn2">
                        <persName corresp="#p_S16">Stalin</persName>’s reply, dated January 23, as
                        received by the President in translation, included the statements, “I do not
                        have any objections against your proposals” and “The same reply I sent to
                        the Prime Minister’s request” (Roosevelt Papers).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
